FORMER Kaizer Chiefs player Pule Ekstein has joined Azerbaijan SIDE Sabah FC on a two-year contract. Ekstein started his professional career at Chiefs and was developed before he was promoted to the first team at the beginning of 2014/2015 season by Stuart Baxter who was the coach by then. His contract come to an end on 30 June but the two parties agreed to terminate it in April when they couldn't reach a breakthrough during negotiations. Reports suggest that Absa Premiership side Cape Town City were interested on signing the player, but he ended up choosing the overseas move where he will be playing for Sabah. Sabah narrowly escaped relegation after finishing seventh in the eight-team league last season.  